summary: A long time ago I have been called crazy in my private life, because i refused to let go of a certain belief, even though I had...
body:
A long time ago I have been called crazy in my private life, because i refused to let go of a certain belief, even though I had no proof at the time. It was heartbreaking and I doubted myself every day back then. Turns out years later, 
I was right all along. 

Since that time I have learned always to listen to my gut feeling and if something doesn’t seems to add up, to question it. And that’s why I am here today.

summary: Okay but like what was up with that random happy birthday tweet louis sent out on harry's bday in 2017 like...what? Do you think...
question: Okay but like what was up with that random happy birthday tweet louis sent out on harry's bday in 2017 like...what? Do you think it was like an attempt to reach out or? Maybe because Robin passing it was like extending an olive branch of some sorts.
answer:
Hello anon!

I dont think they were ever on bad terms (or enemies), if that is what you are talking about. I think they just had kind of different views on the whole relationship and it becoming public. And even more so, I think the final straw on the relationship was Louis getting a girl pregnant (sorry!).

But as @whenhazzametlou suggested numerous times, I believe they had this on-off thing from time to time (maybe even strictly physical). Like around the time of Jay’s passing, and probably around the time of Robin’s passing, too. Actually I think they actual reconnection was when Jay passed away.

So to answer your question, I dont think there was a need for an olive branch as I don’t think they fell out to that extreme. I believe they were still very much in contact, and that a lot went down behind the scenes (and that we didnt actually witness any of it). But it was kind of a denial of the ‘arch nemessis larry’ narrative, and I salute Louis for that! Haha

summary: I agree with what you say about Larry. I think the "least close with" and "mutual respect" part was unnecessary but it's Dan...
question: I agree with what you say about Larry. I think the "least close with" and "mutual respect" part was unnecessary but it's Dan Wootton so. The only part I really truly hate about the interview is the part where Louis says he's concerned about the people who believe in Larry because that makes us sound like a bunch of wierdos with a fetish for gay couples or sth and I know Louis didn't mean it and he was obviously a little nervous and uncomfortable talking about Larry but that really hurt .
answer:
Hello anon! I think this is the best we could get having in mind that he can’t confirm confirm it.. but this is definitely not the way you talk about someone you used to be friends with. As someone said, this is ex-boyfriend talk.

I dont think Louis was ever, say, all in on the Larry thing or even comfortable with it because despite popular belief I dont think they were forsed into closet… But getting even this bit of information, and the way he said it makes me think that he is coming to terms with the whole larry talk.

Actually another thing I want to say on this matter is that I dont think Louis is even remotely angry with people believing in Larry. I mean, if they were ever together (which I believe they were) and if they broke up (which I believe they did), of course it stings a bit when someone mentions it. It sometimes stings me to talk about an ex I broke up years ago, so I get that. But imagine still having an army of people who believe you are married to that ex and that your child is a doll? I would be pissed, too.

The bottom line is that I dont think Louis hates us at all but he is human after all, he has feelings and we probably sometimes hurt him. But I still dont think there is anything wrong with believing in Larry as long as you dont go around harrasing people Louis cares about.
